- This is yummy.

98
00:06:58,390 --> 00:06:59,560
Goodness! Fine then!

99
00:07:09,570 --> 00:07:10,570
What's wrong?

100
00:07:11,470 --> 00:07:13,870
I won't have any regrets.

101
00:07:15,470 --> 00:07:18,480
I know. You're not like that.

102
00:07:18,810 --> 00:07:20,330
Because I'm going to say it right now.

103
00:07:22,550 --> 00:07:23,610
What?

104
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:24,950
Right now.

105
00:07:26,380 --> 00:07:27,590
I'm going to tell you.

106
00:07:28,890 --> 00:07:29,890
How I feel.

107
00:07:30,990 --> 00:07:32,590
No way. It can't be, can it?

108
00:07:34,490 --> 00:07:37,160
Gosh, this is going to
be so awkward if he does.

109
00:07:54,980 --> 00:07:59,750
- I'm going to go check on Yi Rang.
- Wait, Mom. Take this too.

110
00:07:59,850 --> 00:08:02,890
- Okay.
- That looks heavy. Let me take it.

111
00:08:04,260 --> 00:08:05,566
- I'll go with her.
- Okay.

112
00:08:05,590 --> 00:08:07,630
Grandma, me too! Me too!

113
00:08:08,590 --> 00:08:11,030
Me too. I want to go too.

114
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:16,230
- Isn't that heavy?
- No! I want to go too! Me too!

115
00:08:16,870 --> 00:08:19,800
Don't you ever wonder
about your mom and dad?

116
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:22,340
I'm not really sure.

117
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:24,910
I can't remember them.

118
00:08:26,780 --> 00:08:27,780
I see.

119
00:08:30,450 --> 00:08:33,350
By the way, what's that in your pocket?

120
00:08:34,650 --> 00:08:36,990
What? What's this?

121
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:39,360
A golf ball?

122
00:08:40,490 --> 00:08:42,690
Can I see that for a second?

123
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:44,160
Here?

124
00:08:47,430 --> 00:08:49,170
Hey... Where did he go?

125
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:53,240
I see.

126
00:08:54,210 --> 00:08:57,140
I guess this was the last thing you held.

127
00:08:57,710 --> 00:08:58,910
I see.

128
00:08:59,610 --> 00:09:01,710
Can I get a closer look at that ball?

129
00:09:03,980 --> 00:09:05,150
GSG?

130
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,920
Uncle!

131
00:09:09,620 --> 00:09:12,890
- Da Bong Bong!
- Ta-da! We're here!

132
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:19,060
Gosh, she's so cute.

133
00:09:43,090 --> 00:09:44,590
Uncle, what's wrong?

134
00:09:48,890 --> 00:09:50,330
Do you like Hachuping?

135
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:54,170
You already know I do. Why ask?

136
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:03,980
I'll give you my love! Hachu, Hachu, ch

137
00:10:04,940 --> 00:10:06,716
- I'll give you lots and lots.
- I'll give you lots and lots.

138
00:10:06,740 --> 00:10:08,610
Hachu, hachu chuchu - Hachu, hachu chuchu.

139
00:10:08,850 --> 00:10:11,626
- It's Hachuping Time, full of love.
- It's Hachuping Time, full of love.

140
00:10:11,650 --> 00:10:15,490
- Hachuchu, hachu, Hachuping!
- Hachuchu, hachu, Hachuping!

141
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:23,360
- It's Hachuping Time, full of love.
- It's Hachuping Time, full of love.

142
00:10:23,490 --> 00:10:26,230
- Chuchu, hachu, Hachuping!
- Chuchu, hachu, Hachuping!

143
00:10:28,030 --> 00:10:30,800
- Hachuping Power!
- Hachuping Power!

144
00:10:30,940 --> 00:10:33,670
- Snap out of it.
- No, wait.

145
00:10:34,340 --> 00:10:36,640
- We have to feed the kids.
- Chuchu, hachu, Hachuping...

146
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:38,010
All right, you two.

147
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:42,480
- Let's eat first, then we can play again!
- Yes!

148
00:10:43,210 --> 00:10:45,090
- Gosh, this looks so good!
- It looks so good!

149
00:10:46,420 --> 00:10:48,450
- This is great.
- Dig in, everyone.

150
00:10:49,890 --> 00:10:51,120
I'll have this.

151
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:53,720
It's so yummy.

152
00:10:54,830 --> 00:10:55,830
This is good.

153
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:11,840
Good morning.

154
00:11:14,650 --> 00:11:15,650
Good morning.

155
00:11:18,950 --> 00:11:20,850
I know a really fun playground.

156
00:11:23,050 --> 00:11:24,160
Good morning.

157
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:40,780
What's with you, Yi Rang?
You're kind of creeping me out.

158
00:11:42,610 --> 00:11:43,870
Am I scawy?

159
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:47,910
She says I'm scary.

160
00:11:48,210 --> 00:11:51,480
- Na-na na-na boo-boo.
- Na-na na-na boo-boo.

161
00:11:51,650 --> 00:11:54,720
- The grown-up's a big scaredy-cat!
- The grown-up's a big scaredy-cat!

162
00:11:57,960 --> 00:12:02,160
- Lightning Man, let's go!
- Let's go!

163
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:06,660
Da Bong! Wait! Oh, hi.

164
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:09,406
If that's an act, he deserves an Oscar.

165
00:12:09,430 --> 00:12:11,440
Looks like we've got a handful this time.

166
00:12:11,740 --> 00:12:16,170
I'll be on my way then. Wait
up, let's go together, okay? Gosh.

167
00:12:17,210 --> 00:12:18,410
I know.

168
00:12:19,380 --> 00:12:21,340
I know, but I just can't
seem to get used to him.

169
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:28,190
- Let's go!
- Gosh.

170
00:12:28,820 --> 00:12:31,966
- Be careful! Gosh, this is fun.
- Mom!

171
00:12:31,990 --> 00:12:33,960
- Lightning Power!
- Come on.

172
00:12:34,020 --> 00:12:36,060
Auntie, you know what?

173
00:12:37,060 --> 00:12:39,900
My uncle is the sweetest
person in the whole world.

174
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:41,600
Sweet?

175
00:12:42,370 --> 00:12:44,100
Do you even know what that word means?

176
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,570
It means understanding how someone feels.

177
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:52,510
When I'm upset, my uncle cries with me,

178
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:56,550
and when I'm happy,
he gets all excited too.

179
00:12:57,850 --> 00:12:59,850
And that's not an easy
thing to do, you know.

180
00:13:02,850 --> 00:13:05,160
That's why my uncle's my favorite person.

181
00:13:20,670 --> 00:13:24,610
By the way, why do you
look at my uncle that way?

182
00:13:26,410 --> 00:13:29,180
Me? How was I looking at him?

183
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:33,420
It's the way my mom looks at my dad.

184
00:13:34,290 --> 00:13:35,550
With kind eyes.

185
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:37,250
With loving eyes.

186
00:13:37,990 --> 00:13:39,120
No, I wasn't.

187
00:13:44,090 --> 00:13:45,660
Slow down.

188
00:13:46,430 --> 00:13:47,746
- Lightning Power!
- You're in our territory!

189
00:13:47,770 --> 00:13:49,100
You're not allowed in here.

190
00:13:54,770 --> 00:13:56,416
- You okay, Yi Rang?
- Uncle!

191
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,380
- What?
- Yi Rang, are you all right?

192
00:13:58,610 --> 00:14:00,440
Why am I... What am I doing here?

193
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:04,010
Come on out. Careful. Be careful.

194
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:11,320
Na Hyun.

195
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:15,290
Are you just going to play around all day?

196
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:18,460
I mean...

197
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:22,700
Aren't you going to work?
You have a job to do.

198
00:14:25,740 --> 00:14:28,340
You okay, man?

199
00:14:28,870 --> 00:14:32,880
- Uncle.
- Da Bong. Why is she so angry?

200
00:14:34,250 --> 00:14:36,450
She was fine when she was with me.

201
00:14:37,650 --> 00:14:39,880
Maybe it's because you
were teasing her earlier?

202
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:44,050
What? You think I was teasing Lawyer Han?

203
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:48,430
You don't remember? You were
going, "Na-na na-na boo-boo."

204
00:14:48,990 --> 00:14:50,190
You were wiggling your butt.

205
00:14:50,760 --> 00:14:55,270
- What?
- "Na-na na-na boo-boo," like this.

206
00:14:55,430 --> 00:14:56,770
I really did that?

207
00:14:57,670 --> 00:15:00,640
Okay, that's enough. But
you also did this too. Like this.

208
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:19,790
What did she mean about
the way I looked at Yi Rang?

209
00:15:28,900 --> 00:15:29,900
I'm here.

210
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:33,640
That was fast.

211
00:15:35,610 --> 00:15:36,610
Yes.

212
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:41,650
By any chance...

213
00:15:42,910 --> 00:15:45,020
- Are you mad at me?
- Why would I be mad?

214
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:47,350
Earlier I

215
00:15:50,690 --> 00:15:53,660
- was messing with you.
- I know you were possessed. Why be mad?

216
00:15:56,390 --> 00:15:59,030
But is it okay for you to
get possessed so often?

217
00:16:00,900 --> 00:16:01,970
What?

218
00:16:02,230 --> 00:16:05,570
In movies, when people see spirits,

219
00:16:06,540 --> 00:16:07,940
it takes a toll on their bodies.

220
00:16:10,570 --> 00:16:12,040
Well, it's nothing like that.

221
00:16:12,580 --> 00:16:14,610
The ghosts I meet

222
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:17,650
aren't that different from regular people.

223
00:16:25,290 --> 00:16:27,060
Did you learn anything about the kid?

224
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:30,030
He had a golf ball.

225
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,200
A golf ball?

226
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:38,040
Yes, the initials GSG were on the ball,

227
00:16:38,770 --> 00:16:40,470
but I'm not sure what it means.

228
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:44,940
Golf clubs put their initials on
golf balls so they don't lose them.

229
00:16:45,510 --> 00:16:46,750
Maybe it's something like that?

230
00:16:48,780 --> 00:16:50,050
That makes sense.

231
00:16:51,550 --> 00:16:55,490
If the kid found the golf
ball right before he died,

232
00:16:55,850 --> 00:16:58,920
it could be a huge clue
as to where he died.

233
00:16:59,260 --> 00:17:01,560
(Seoul, GSG, Seocho-dong,
Golf Driving Range)

234
00:17:01,660 --> 00:17:03,730
(Attorney Shin Yi Rang)

235
00:17:07,230 --> 00:17:10,800
Were there always this many
driving ranges in the heart of Seoul?

236
00:17:12,670 --> 00:17:14,270
This isn't going to work.

237
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:24,650
Do you have any other ideas?

238
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:26,720
No.

239
00:17:30,150 --> 00:17:32,290
Do you have something to say to me?

240
00:17:33,090 --> 00:17:34,930
No, I don't.

241
00:17:37,060 --> 00:17:39,660
You look like you have
something on your mind.

242
00:17:42,930 --> 00:17:46,100
What were you going to say
yesterday at the Sky Park?

243
00:17:47,670 --> 00:17:48,670
What?

244
00:17:49,340 --> 00:17:52,110
That lady. She was really scary.

245
00:17:53,010 --> 00:17:55,810
She got mad and glared at me.

246
00:17:58,920 --> 00:18:00,020
That...

247
00:18:01,350 --> 00:18:02,550
It's nothing.

248
00:18:03,890 --> 00:18:04,990
Really.

249
00:18:05,820 --> 00:18:06,820
It's absolutely nothing.

250
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:09,760
Don't worry about it.

251
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:13,960
Where did I put that golf ball?

252
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:17,000
Here... No, it's not here.

253
00:18:19,270 --> 00:18:21,840
Here? Where's the ball?

254
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:24,440
What was that about?

255
00:18:25,780 --> 00:18:27,480
So it really was nothing.

256
00:18:29,610 --> 00:18:32,620
(Shin Yi Rang and Han Na Hyun Law Office)

257
00:18:41,730 --> 00:18:43,730
(Dance Studio)

258
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:46,530
(Seoul Manpower)

259
00:18:59,310 --> 00:19:02,410
- Dad?
- Na Hyun. Are you off work?

260
00:19:02,810 --> 00:19:04,310
No, not yet. What's up?

261
00:19:04,750 --> 00:19:06,420
The thing is...

262
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:08,650
You know the CEO of Taebaek?

263
00:19:09,290 --> 00:19:10,290
Yang Do Kyung?

264
00:19:10,450 --> 00:19:14,360
Yes. He called me a little while ago.

265
00:19:16,560 --> 00:19:19,760
Hello, sir. This is Yang Do
Kyung, the CEO of Taebaek.

266
00:19:20,300 --> 00:19:22,530
We met once before in
front of Lawyer Han's office...

267
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:26,370
Yes. Hello, sir.

268
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:29,370
Please, sir. No need to be so formal.

269
00:19:29,470 --> 00:19:30,990
I'm a close friend of your daughter's.

270
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:33,240
Please, just call me Do Kyung.

271
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:37,380
Goodness. I couldn't possibly do that.

272
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:40,350
The reason I'm calling

273
00:19:40,650 --> 00:19:42,366
I was just calling to check on you,

274
00:19:42,390 --> 00:19:44,230
and see how you're
feeling since the accident.

275
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:47,690
I'm perfectly fine. Nothing's wrong at all.

276
00:19:48,190 --> 00:19:49,530
That's a relief.

277
00:19:51,060 --> 00:19:52,830
But the thing about car accidents is...

278
00:19:53,630 --> 00:19:57,570
You might feel fine now, but later
on, you can start aching all over.

279
00:19:57,730 --> 00:19:59,370
It can easily lead to chronic pain.

280
00:20:00,070 --> 00:20:03,470
No, really, I'm perfectly fine.

281
00:20:03,670 --> 00:20:05,880
No, I'm not okay with it, sir.

282
00:20:07,610 --> 00:20:11,420
You're Lawyer Han's father. We've
been through thick and thin for years.

283
00:20:12,050 --> 00:20:14,530
I can't just leave this in the
hands of the insurance company.

284
00:20:15,220 --> 00:20:18,720
As it happens, there's a great
acupuncture clinic near my company.

285
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:21,040
So, what does your schedule
look like tomorrow, sir?

286
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:24,290
So, before I knew it,

287
00:20:24,730 --> 00:20:27,060
I ended up making an
appointment for three tomorrow.

288
00:20:27,430 --> 00:20:29,270
Why does Mr. Yang
keep doing things like that?

289
00:20:29,630 --> 00:20:30,830
Na Hyun.

290
00:20:31,270 --> 00:20:34,270
Is there something going on
between you and Mr. Yang?

291
00:20:34,640 --> 00:20:37,320
What do you mean, "something"?
There's nothing. Absolutely nothing.

292
00:20:37,770 --> 00:20:40,680
Then I guess he's just a really nice guy?

293
00:20:41,710 --> 00:20:45,750
Dad, call Mr. Yang right now and
tell him you're not going. Got it?

294
00:20:45,950 --> 00:20:49,920
Okay, fine. I will. All right. Take care.

295
00:20:50,020 --> 00:20:51,920
(Available)

296
00:21:00,830 --> 00:21:04,600
- Yes, sir?
- I don't think I should go after all.

297
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:06,300
You're not coming?

298
00:21:06,940 --> 00:21:09,310
- Why the sudden change of heart?
- It's just.

299
00:21:09,940 --> 00:21:14,110
I'm not really hurting
anywhere. And I'm a bit busy too.

300
00:21:15,310 --> 00:21:18,150
- And also...
- There isn't some other reason, is there?

301
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:23,050
It's Na Hyun.

302
00:21:23,950 --> 00:21:25,060
Lawyer Han?

303
00:21:27,460 --> 00:21:30,190
My daughter isn't happy about it.

304
00:21:31,530 --> 00:21:35,400
I'm sorry, Mr. Yang. I just
got a fare, so I have to go.

305
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:37,530
- I'm sorry.
- Sir, wait, that's not...

306
00:21:37,800 --> 00:21:38,800
Hello?

307
00:21:39,740 --> 00:21:40,740
Sir?

308
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:47,640
Goodness.

309
00:21:50,180 --> 00:21:53,150
(Pit-a-Pat Butcher Restaurant)

310
00:22:05,330 --> 00:22:07,760
- Chief Prosecutor.
- Oh, hi.

311
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:09,700
What brings you here?

312
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:12,400
I came hoping to get a bite to eat,

313
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:15,070
but are you already closed for the day?

314
00:22:15,410 --> 00:22:20,010
I'm so sorry. Today's our regular day off.

315
00:22:20,980 --> 00:22:23,680
That can't be helped. I'll
come back another time.

316
00:22:25,020 --> 00:22:26,020
Wait.

317
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:31,760
Actually, I've been wanting
to treat you to a meal.

318
00:22:32,090 --> 00:22:33,460
Why don't you come to my home?

319
00:22:33,690 --> 00:22:36,290
No, I couldn't. I wouldn't
want to impose so suddenly.

320
00:22:36,360 --> 00:22:39,400
No, not at all. Honestly,
I'd feel better if you did.

321
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:41,200
Let's go.

322
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:44,100
If you insist. Thank you.

323
00:22:52,210 --> 00:22:54,010
Please, take your time and eat up.

324
00:22:54,310 --> 00:22:57,280
I'm just going to go finish
cleaning up at the restaurant.

325
00:22:57,410 --> 00:23:00,150
- Of course, take your time.
- Okay.

326
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:02,186
Excuse me... Are you looking for something?

327
00:24:02,210 --> 00:24:05,980
No. I just finished eating,
and I couldn't find you.

328
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:10,520
I'm sorry. I brought you
here and just left you.

329
00:24:10,620 --> 00:24:13,160
Not at all. It's my fault for
dropping by unannounced.

330
00:24:13,260 --> 00:24:15,730
Thanks to you, I had a wonderful meal.

331
00:24:16,660 --> 00:24:19,300
- I'm so glad.
- I'll come by again sometime.

332
00:24:19,530 --> 00:24:20,530
Of course, please do.

333
00:24:21,330 --> 00:24:23,300
(Pit-a-Pat Butcher Restaurant)

334
00:24:39,820 --> 00:24:41,050
Darn.

335
00:25:10,980 --> 00:25:12,150
Excuse me...

336
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:14,280
Are you looking for something?

337
00:25:14,350 --> 00:25:18,120
No. I just finished eating,
and I couldn't find you.

338
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:21,220
Wait, why was he in the master bedroom?

339
00:25:23,790 --> 00:25:24,930
By any chance...

340
00:25:25,830 --> 00:25:28,070
Are there any files that Ki
Jung might have left behind?

341
00:25:28,700 --> 00:25:33,040
- Files?
- Case files, like Ki Jung's notebook...

342
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:36,040
The key evidence related to the
case was nowhere to be found.

343
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:47,320
(Attorney Shin Yi Rang)

344
00:25:51,290 --> 00:25:53,120
Good Shot Golf?

345
00:25:56,530 --> 00:25:59,030
(Good Shot Golf Driving Range)

346
00:26:07,740 --> 00:26:09,810
- I found it.
- Really?

347
00:26:10,670 --> 00:26:13,710
Does that mean you can
find my mom and dad now?

348
00:26:15,650 --> 00:26:19,080
It's too late tonight, so let's go
home and get some sleep first.

349
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:22,190
We'll meet with Na Hyun
tomorrow and talk it over.

350
00:26:23,450 --> 00:26:27,360
But can I stay with Grandma?

351
00:26:28,530 --> 00:26:29,630
Why with her?

352
00:26:29,990 --> 00:26:32,230
Because I like being with Grandma.

353
00:26:35,130 --> 00:26:36,900
Okay. Let's do that.

354
00:26:37,300 --> 00:26:38,670
Oh, yes!

355
00:26:45,180 --> 00:26:46,380
Just a little longer.

356
00:26:47,110 --> 00:26:48,210
I promise,

357
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:50,280
find your mom for you soon.

358
00:26:56,850 --> 00:26:57,850
Darn it!

359
00:26:58,590 --> 00:27:00,710
The more I think about it,
the more pissed off I get.

360
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:14,070
She's not here yet.

361
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:21,910
"Not a big deal?" Is he kidding me?

362
00:27:29,950 --> 00:27:33,090
(Attorney Shin Yi Rang)

363
00:27:34,520 --> 00:27:36,920
The person you've called is
not available. After the tone...

364
00:27:41,100 --> 00:27:43,430
It's not like Na Hyun to be late.

365
00:27:43,800 --> 00:27:45,400
Who's Na Hyun?

366
00:27:47,140 --> 00:27:50,370
The woman from Sky Park and the playground?

367
00:27:50,510 --> 00:27:52,030
The one you said got really mad at me.

368
00:27:52,210 --> 00:27:56,580
No. The one who got mad
was the doggy's owner.

369
00:27:57,310 --> 00:28:00,850
She was yelling about
how you scared her dog.

370
00:28:02,150 --> 00:28:05,060
What? So it wasn't Na Hyun who got mad?

371
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:09,890
Actually, she was looking at you
like she was expecting something.

372
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:14,260
Like a kid about to open
a Christmas present.

373
00:28:16,830 --> 00:28:17,830
Na Hyun

374
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:20,400
was expecting something?

375
00:28:23,310 --> 00:28:26,110
What? I was worried for nothing.

376
00:28:28,410 --> 00:28:30,250
(Attorney Han Na Hyun)

377
00:28:33,480 --> 00:28:35,650
Is she running late because it's awkward?

378
00:28:57,040 --> 00:28:59,110
(Shin Yi Rang and Han Na Hyun Law Office)

379
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:13,960
I'm here.

380
00:29:26,970 --> 00:29:27,970
Yes?

381
00:29:33,180 --> 00:29:34,240
How can I help you?

382
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:43,950
Ma'am, please, how can I help you?

383
00:29:44,150 --> 00:29:47,460
My child... My child is missing!

384
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:50,836
Please find my child!

385
00:29:50,860 --> 00:29:52,976
- Please, you have to find him.
- Please calm down, ma'am. Okay?

386
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:55,770
Please find my child. Please.

387
00:29:55,970 --> 00:29:57,050
You're looking for a child?

388
00:29:57,530 --> 00:29:59,540
I think he's in 1st or 2nd grade,

389
00:29:59,740 --> 00:30:02,340
and had an accident at
Good Shot Golf Range.

390
00:30:02,810 --> 00:30:04,010
One moment.

391
00:30:09,050 --> 00:30:10,050
Stay still...

392
00:30:11,580 --> 00:30:14,680
But the Good Shot Golf Driving
Range has been closed since 2020.

393
00:30:14,820 --> 00:30:16,520
And there are no accident reports on file.

394
00:30:17,250 --> 00:30:20,060
Then what about any records
of a child in yellow rain boots?

395
00:30:20,690 --> 00:30:23,230
I was hoping you'd focus
on that fatal accident.

396
00:30:28,130 --> 00:30:30,430
(Case search: No matching data found)

397
00:30:30,630 --> 00:30:31,970
There's nothing on that either.

398
00:30:32,470 --> 00:30:34,140
So, why are you asking about this?

399
00:30:34,700 --> 00:30:36,300
Is this related to a crime or something?

400
00:30:36,940 --> 00:30:39,310
I'm not sure about that myself.

401
00:30:40,810 --> 00:30:43,080
Okay, I understand. Thank you.

402
00:30:45,350 --> 00:30:47,020
Lightning Man! Let's go.

403
00:30:53,260 --> 00:30:55,060
Is that guy a little off?

404
00:31:04,200 --> 00:31:06,000
When do we get to see Da Bong?

405
00:31:06,470 --> 00:31:07,800
Later this evening.

406
00:31:09,770 --> 00:31:11,740
But I want to play with her now.

407
00:31:15,580 --> 00:31:17,850
(Good Shot Golf Driving Range)

408
00:31:20,480 --> 00:31:22,840
(This location is permanently
closed or has no information)

409
00:31:25,020 --> 00:31:26,520
Guess I'll just have to go myself.

410
00:31:31,560 --> 00:31:34,030
Should we get something tasty to eat?

411
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:37,846
- What do you like? Burgers? Pizza?
- Pizza!

412
00:31:37,870 --> 00:31:40,640
Pizza? I love pizza too.

413
00:31:47,210 --> 00:31:50,180
Well, you're the first ghost I've
met who has the same taste as me.

414
00:31:51,850 --> 00:31:56,426
Lightning Man, listen to me carefully.
Later, when you smell the pizza,

415
00:31:56,450 --> 00:31:59,820
just like at the playground,
you're going to become me.

416
00:31:59,890 --> 00:32:03,590
Then you can eat all the
delicious pizza you want. Got it?

417
00:32:03,690 --> 00:32:04,730
Okay.

418
00:32:05,500 --> 00:32:07,030
What kind should we get?

419
00:32:08,330 --> 00:32:10,376
- Sweet potato?
- Sweet potato!

420
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:11,900
- Bulgogi?
- Bulgogi.

421
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:15,610
Let's go!

422
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:28,480
I want to divorce

423
00:32:30,890 --> 00:32:32,160
my wife.

424
00:32:34,190 --> 00:32:38,260
May I ask the reason
you're seeking a divorce?

425
00:32:38,630 --> 00:32:39,930
When my wife is with me,

426
00:32:42,630 --> 00:32:43,630
she suffers.

427
00:32:45,740 --> 00:32:46,900
To protect my wife...

428
00:32:49,010 --> 00:32:50,040
This is the only way.

429
00:33:13,230 --> 00:33:15,330
Hey, thanks for the food.

430
00:33:15,630 --> 00:33:17,930
Lightning Man, after you finish the pizza,

431
00:33:18,130 --> 00:33:20,500
just splash a little water
on your face. Got it?

432
00:33:30,180 --> 00:33:32,780
Gosh, he actually ate the whole thing.

433
00:33:33,850 --> 00:33:35,520
It was so, so good.

434
00:33:37,020 --> 00:33:39,760
Good. I'm just glad you're happy.

435
00:33:42,860 --> 00:33:46,260
I'm just going to wash my
hands. Wait right here, okay?

436
00:34:02,310 --> 00:34:03,780
Hello there.

437
00:34:04,250 --> 00:34:05,350
Detective.

438
00:34:05,850 --> 00:34:09,120
You're a little early. It'll
be about five more minutes.

439
00:34:09,190 --> 00:34:10,720
That's fine. I don't mind waiting.

440
00:34:11,320 --> 00:34:14,060
Okay. You know, seeing
as you buy one every day,

441
00:34:14,160 --> 00:34:16,130
your son must really love pizza.

442
00:34:16,230 --> 00:34:20,030
Yes. He especially loves your pizza.

443
00:34:20,130 --> 00:34:21,500
That's great to hear.

444
00:34:21,700 --> 00:34:24,540
You should bring him by sometime.
I'll throw in something on the house.

445
00:34:25,300 --> 00:34:27,870
I'd love to, but he's really
shy around strangers.

446
00:34:28,040 --> 00:34:29,710
At that age, they're all...

447
00:34:30,210 --> 00:34:33,780
- Can I pay?
- Yes, that'll be 42 dollars.

448
00:34:33,880 --> 00:34:35,450
That was delicious. Thank you.

449
00:34:37,180 --> 00:34:38,180
Counselor?

450
00:34:39,750 --> 00:34:40,750
Sorry?

451
00:34:41,320 --> 00:34:42,520
You don't remember me?

452
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:45,240
I'm Detective Jo Chi Yeong
from the Seocho Police Station.

453
00:34:46,520 --> 00:34:48,590
Shin Yi Rang, your
lawyer is here to see you.

454
00:34:54,100 --> 00:34:56,030
Hey, you have a cop friend?

455
00:34:56,730 --> 00:35:01,340
- So cool!
- When you were in for juvenile assault,

456
00:35:01,400 --> 00:35:02,570
we met back then.

457
00:35:03,540 --> 00:35:06,180
Hey, who did you hit?

458
00:35:07,310 --> 00:35:10,410
Detective, about that... They
were the aggressors, remember?

459
00:35:11,080 --> 00:35:13,820
That's right. My apologies.
It was a slip of the tongue.

460
00:35:13,920 --> 00:35:15,180
No, don't worry about it.

461
00:35:16,450 --> 00:35:19,050
Since you're in the Detective
Division, you might know something.

462
00:35:19,320 --> 00:35:21,636
I'm looking for a boy
who had an accident

463
00:35:21,660 --> 00:35:23,660
at the Good Shot Golf Driving Range,

464
00:35:24,260 --> 00:35:25,860
do you happen to know anything about it?

465
00:35:26,130 --> 00:35:29,770
- At the Good Shot Golf Driving Range?
- Yes, he's about

466
00:35:30,430 --> 00:35:35,140
a 1st or 2nd grader. He was
wearing yellow rain boots.

467
00:35:37,040 --> 00:35:40,140
Let me see. I don't recall a case like that.

468
00:35:40,710 --> 00:35:41,710
Why? What's this about?

469
00:35:43,050 --> 00:35:47,720
I know the kid, but he
can't remember the accident.

470
00:35:48,520 --> 00:35:50,320
So I was just wondering
if you knew anything.

471
00:35:51,420 --> 00:35:54,260
- It's okay if you don't.
- All right, you're all set.

472
00:35:54,690 --> 00:35:57,160
Okay. I'll be going then.

473
00:35:57,660 --> 00:35:59,400
- Take care, Counselor.
- You too.

474
00:36:13,080 --> 00:36:16,350
Hey, Senior Officer Lee, did any
missing person reports come in?

475
00:36:16,450 --> 00:36:19,150
Oh? Yes, I was just about to tell you, sir.

476
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:22,040
A report for a missing elementary
student came in a little while ago.

477
00:36:22,220 --> 00:36:25,490
- An elementary schooler?
- Yes, an 8-year-old 1st grader.

478
00:36:26,460 --> 00:36:30,260
- Description?
- White sweatshirt and yellow rain boots.

479
00:36:32,500 --> 00:36:36,930
A boy, maybe 1st or 2nd grade,
and he was wearing yellow rain boots.

480
00:36:39,740 --> 00:36:41,400
Text me all the details.

481
00:36:41,970 --> 00:36:44,040
- Yes, sir.
- Okay.

482
00:36:46,380 --> 00:36:48,980
(Pit-a-Pat Butcher Restaurant,
Shin Yi Rang Law Office)

483
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:03,360
My son overslept that day.

484
00:37:05,130 --> 00:37:06,800
He normally wakes up with no problem,

485
00:37:07,730 --> 00:37:09,890
but for some reason, he
just couldn't get up that day.

486
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:13,740
I felt his forehead, and
he had a slight fever.

487
00:37:14,940 --> 00:37:17,340
- Go on, get your shoes.
- All right, I'm heading out. Okay.

488
00:37:17,570 --> 00:37:19,810
- My wife leaves for work earlier than me.
- Si Ho.

489
00:37:20,280 --> 00:37:22,280
So I was the one who got
our son ready for school.

490
00:37:26,420 --> 00:37:29,050
But I couldn't suddenly take
the day off because he was sick.

491
00:37:29,520 --> 00:37:32,920
Si Ho, Daddy's got an
idea. Hold on a second.

492
00:37:33,160 --> 00:37:34,460
So to cheer him up,

493
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:36,830
I got out his yellow rain boots.

494
00:37:38,330 --> 00:37:40,050
It just so happened to be raining that day,

495
00:37:40,900 --> 00:37:43,200
Ta-da! He loved wearing his rain boots.

496
00:37:44,530 --> 00:37:46,970
Open the door, then the
umbrella 1st. Umbrella 1st.

497
00:37:50,440 --> 00:37:53,710
Have a good day at school,
Si Ho. Okay, close the door.

498
00:37:55,340 --> 00:37:56,540
Hurry on, go meet your friend.

499
00:38:02,720 --> 00:38:03,720
Go on.

500
00:38:10,490 --> 00:38:11,610
I never would've imagined

501
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:15,960
that it would be the
last time I saw my son.

502
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:21,900
The last time?

503
00:38:22,840 --> 00:38:24,510
Like most couples who both work,

504
00:38:26,010 --> 00:38:28,910
my wife and I took
turns picking up our son.

505
00:38:29,810 --> 00:38:31,250
That day, it was my wife's turn.

506
00:38:32,180 --> 00:38:33,250
But then...

507
00:38:34,080 --> 00:38:37,950
(Yongjin Express, Fast
Delivery, Same-Day Delivery)

508
00:38:39,490 --> 00:38:42,560
Can you pick up our son today? Sorry.

509
00:38:45,830 --> 00:38:47,760
(School Bus Stop. Child Safety Zone)

510
00:38:48,460 --> 00:38:52,400
(Yongjin Express)

511
00:38:55,570 --> 00:38:57,710
By the time I saw her text and rushed over,

512
00:38:59,080 --> 00:39:00,686
My son was already gone.

513
00:39:00,710 --> 00:39:01,740
Si Ho!

514
00:39:03,980 --> 00:39:05,110
Si Ho!

515
00:39:06,520 --> 00:39:07,520
Si Ho!

516
00:39:08,180 --> 00:39:09,190
Si Ho!

517
00:39:11,720 --> 00:39:12,720
Si Ho!

518
00:39:13,990 --> 00:39:16,230
Si Ho!

519
00:39:18,390 --> 00:39:19,500
Si Ho!

520
00:39:20,700 --> 00:39:21,800
Si Ho!

521
00:39:22,930 --> 00:39:23,930
Si Ho!

522
00:39:24,530 --> 00:39:27,846
Excuse me! Sir, have you
seen a boy about this tall?

523
00:39:27,870 --> 00:39:29,940
He was wearing a blue backpack,

524
00:39:30,310 --> 00:39:32,540
He's in the first grade, and
he wore yellow rain boots.

525
00:39:32,910 --> 00:39:34,390
He was wearing his yellow rain boots.

526
00:39:34,880 --> 00:39:35,880
Have you seen him?

527
00:39:36,480 --> 00:39:39,420
- Sorry, I haven't.
- Si Ho!

528
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:43,850
Yoon Si Ho!

529
00:39:46,960 --> 00:39:48,190
Si Ho!

530
00:39:49,490 --> 00:39:51,590
Where on earth are you?

531
00:39:54,030 --> 00:39:55,460
And so, after our son disappeared,

532
00:39:57,370 --> 00:39:58,370
My wife and I

533
00:40:03,310 --> 00:40:04,590
were plunged into a living hell.

534
00:40:19,860 --> 00:40:22,390
(Pit-a-Pat Butcher Restaurant,
Shin Yi Rang Law Office)

535
00:40:54,190 --> 00:40:56,090
Detective?

536
00:40:58,760 --> 00:41:01,830
I checked, and an elementary
student was in fact reported missing.

537
00:41:02,160 --> 00:41:04,270
So I wanted to talk to you
about it more, Counselor.

538
00:41:04,570 --> 00:41:05,800
Perfect.

539
00:41:06,870 --> 00:41:09,570
In that case, would you
like to look around with me?

540
00:41:10,170 --> 00:41:13,280
I figured searching together would
be faster than for me to explain.

541
00:41:13,880 --> 00:41:16,110
So you think the kid is in here, Counselor?

542
00:41:18,650 --> 00:41:21,720
Yes. I can't get into the specifics,

543
00:41:22,080 --> 00:41:23,640
but I have a strong feeling that he is.

544
00:41:24,620 --> 00:41:26,160
Will you come with me?

545
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:29,400
If a child is in danger,
it's our duty to save him.

546
00:41:30,760 --> 00:41:31,960
- Thank you.
- Of course.

547
00:41:37,500 --> 00:41:39,020
Could you wait here for just a moment?

548
00:41:39,340 --> 00:41:40,340
Sure.

549
00:41:50,510 --> 00:41:54,080
While I go with the police officer,

550
00:41:54,320 --> 00:41:55,920
I need you to wait right here, okay?

551
00:41:56,320 --> 00:41:58,050
Can't I go with you?

552
00:42:01,860 --> 00:42:05,730
You know how some things
on TV are for grown-ups only?

553
00:42:06,200 --> 00:42:07,300
This is one of those times.

554
00:42:08,400 --> 00:42:11,170
It might be dangerous in there for a kid.

555
00:42:13,200 --> 00:42:14,970
But I want to stay with you.

556
00:42:16,040 --> 00:42:17,840
I'll be right back, okay?

557
00:42:18,910 --> 00:42:21,210
I'm scared of being alone.

558
00:42:30,750 --> 00:42:33,190
Here, the Lightning Man.

559
00:42:34,660 --> 00:42:37,530
- Here, why not watch this for a bit?
- Okay.

560
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:50,770
- Shall we go?
- Okay.

561
00:42:51,770 --> 00:42:53,240
You're even getting your gun ready?

562
00:42:54,110 --> 00:42:55,440
You can never be too careful.

563
00:42:56,580 --> 00:42:58,480
I feel much safer with you here, Detective.

564
00:42:59,080 --> 00:43:00,250
- Let's go.
- Okay.

565
00:43:14,900 --> 00:43:19,030
(Good Shot Golf Range, GSG)

566
00:43:27,410 --> 00:43:31,480
(CCTV recording in progress)

567
00:43:36,950 --> 00:43:41,160
By the way, how did you
find out about this place?

568
00:43:45,790 --> 00:43:47,530
You can't tell me that either?

569
00:43:48,400 --> 00:43:51,130
I'm sorry. You wouldn't
believe me even if I told you.

570
00:44:04,280 --> 00:44:06,880
Hey, where are Officer
Park and Sergeant Kim?

571
00:44:07,080 --> 00:44:09,040
They just went out on
a public intoxication call.

572
00:44:10,690 --> 00:44:14,190
Then get ready, Officer Kim. A
missing person report just came in.

573
00:44:14,560 --> 00:44:17,260
- A missing person?
- Yes, it's under an embargo for now,

574
00:44:17,460 --> 00:44:20,100
and there's no evidence of
kidnapping or contact from the culprit.

575
00:44:20,230 --> 00:44:22,230
Start canvassing the
neighborhood for now. Got it?

576
00:44:22,600 --> 00:44:26,370
I emailed you the flyer, so
take a look and print it out. Okay?

577
00:44:29,140 --> 00:44:31,740
(Seocho Police Station: Request
to Circulate Missing Child Flyer)

578
00:44:34,980 --> 00:44:37,280
(Details: Kwon Ye Jun, Male, Age 8)

579
00:44:39,050 --> 00:44:41,720
(Wearing: White sweatshirt,
blue jeans, and yellow rain boots)

580
00:44:43,450 --> 00:44:46,120
Then what about the record for
the child in the yellow rain boots?

581
00:44:46,890 --> 00:44:49,320
You should focus on
that fatal accident case.

582
00:45:06,580 --> 00:45:08,380
Did you hear that?

583
00:45:10,280 --> 00:45:11,826
There's a construction site nearby.

584
00:45:11,850 --> 00:45:13,370
It sounds like it's coming from there.

585
00:45:13,880 --> 00:45:14,880
Is that it?

586
00:45:18,050 --> 00:45:19,150
No, that's not it.

587
00:45:20,490 --> 00:45:21,660
It sounded much closer.

588
00:45:23,760 --> 00:45:27,300
That missing child from earlier,
when was the report filed?

589
00:45:27,830 --> 00:45:30,030
- This morning.
- This morning?

590
00:45:31,530 --> 00:45:32,770
That doesn't make sense.

591
00:45:41,480 --> 00:45:42,480
There's another one.

592
00:45:43,450 --> 00:45:45,610
- What do you mean?
- There's another missing child.

593
00:45:50,220 --> 00:45:51,220
Counselor.

594
00:45:52,050 --> 00:45:53,060
By any chance...

595
00:45:54,220 --> 00:45:57,060
Have you ever been here before,
back when it was a shaman's house?

596
00:45:59,230 --> 00:46:00,430
How did you know that?

597
00:46:01,960 --> 00:46:02,970
The child's ghost.

598
00:46:04,700 --> 00:46:05,806
I'm sorry to ask,

599
00:46:05,830 --> 00:46:08,640
but could you please tell me
your son's name and birthday?

600
00:46:10,270 --> 00:46:11,270
Why do you ask?

601
00:46:12,880 --> 00:46:14,680
Power!

602
00:46:18,080 --> 00:46:19,380
I figured out who the child is.

603
00:46:20,620 --> 00:46:22,650
Born April 16, 2017.

604
00:46:23,590 --> 00:46:24,950
(Yoon Si Ho. Born: April 16, 2017)

605
00:46:27,360 --> 00:46:28,790
Yoon Si Ho.

606
00:46:29,220 --> 00:46:32,190
(Yoon Si Ho)

607
00:46:36,170 --> 00:46:37,500
Butterfly - Butterfly.

608
00:46:38,230 --> 00:46:39,430
Look at him smile.

609
00:46:40,900 --> 00:46:41,900
Goodness.

610
00:46:43,510 --> 00:46:44,710
(Police)

611
00:47:09,800 --> 00:47:11,570
I'm sure I heard it from over here.

612
00:47:26,320 --> 00:47:27,720
Who on earth are you, jerk?

613
00:47:36,360 --> 00:47:37,490
Hey there, kiddo.

614
00:47:40,700 --> 00:47:42,406
What are you doing here?
Shouldn't you be home?

615
00:47:42,430 --> 00:47:45,900
Mister, that cop is dangerous.

616
00:47:47,370 --> 00:47:49,370
- Lieutenant.
- How did you know about this place?

617
00:47:50,710 --> 00:47:53,390
How can you possibly know about
something that happened a year ago!

618
00:47:54,540 --> 00:47:56,310
Help me!

619
00:47:57,110 --> 00:48:00,120
See? Now you've scared the kid.

620
00:48:01,450 --> 00:48:02,550
It was you.

621
00:48:03,850 --> 00:48:05,120
You were the culprit all along.

622
00:48:06,420 --> 00:48:09,090
- Help me!
- My goodness.

623
00:48:38,420 --> 00:48:39,620
Darn it!

624
00:48:45,690 --> 00:48:46,830
Just die.

625
00:48:48,460 --> 00:48:49,530
Hands up!

626
00:48:56,240 --> 00:48:58,910
- I'm Jo Chi Yeong, Seocho Police.
- Show me your ID.

627
00:49:06,050 --> 00:49:07,610
I'm here looking for the missing child.

628
00:49:14,320 --> 00:49:16,560
- Yes, sir.
- Right.

629
00:49:19,560 --> 00:49:22,030
- What about him?
- Him? He's the suspect.

630
00:49:22,430 --> 00:49:24,230
I have to take him in,
so lend me your cuffs.

631
00:49:24,330 --> 00:49:25,330
Yes, sir.

632
00:49:30,670 --> 00:49:33,480
Mister! Snap out of it!

633
00:49:35,710 --> 00:49:36,910
I'll help you.

634
00:49:38,780 --> 00:49:41,250
We have to defeat the bad cop!

635
00:49:43,550 --> 00:49:45,820
Lightning Man, let's go!

636
00:49:47,190 --> 00:49:48,190
No, don't.

637
00:49:50,060 --> 00:49:52,830
You could get hurt again.

638
00:49:54,760 --> 00:49:55,760
Don't.

639
00:49:57,270 --> 00:49:58,270
No, don't.

640
00:50:09,610 --> 00:50:14,380
Excuse me, sir. Is that white
SUV parked outside yours?

641
00:50:15,080 --> 00:50:16,720
Yes. Why?

642
00:50:18,820 --> 00:50:19,890
Never mind, sir.

643
00:50:45,580 --> 00:50:47,880
Lightning Man, change of plans.

644
00:50:48,450 --> 00:50:49,450
Hide.

645
00:50:56,120 --> 00:50:57,330
Darn it.

646
00:50:59,430 --> 00:51:01,130
Where's the other one hiding?

647
00:51:06,030 --> 00:51:07,590
You're not listening to Daddy, are you?

648
00:51:08,600 --> 00:51:09,870
I guess my boy needs a lesson.

649
00:51:47,480 --> 00:51:48,840
What did Daddy tell you?

650
00:51:50,580 --> 00:51:52,740
I told you, good little boys
are supposed to be quiet.

651
00:51:53,280 --> 00:51:54,650
Please, spare me.

652
00:51:56,720 --> 00:51:58,266
I told you, if you just
bear with it a little longer,

653
00:51:58,290 --> 00:51:59,720
you can live with me.

654
00:52:01,090 --> 00:52:02,570
How many times do I have to tell you?

655
00:52:04,390 --> 00:52:06,790
How many more people have
to die before you'll listen to me?

656
00:52:10,630 --> 00:52:12,300
That does it. Come here.

657
00:52:14,540 --> 00:52:15,540
Freeze!

658
00:52:19,470 --> 00:52:21,510
- Power up!
- Power up!

659
00:52:22,140 --> 00:52:26,580
- Lightning! Lightning Power!
- Lightning! Lightning Power!

660
00:52:33,320 --> 00:52:34,720
Justice is served.

661
00:52:35,360 --> 00:52:37,430
Time to change back into a regular guy!

662
00:52:50,440 --> 00:52:52,910
Hey, kiddo. Are you okay?

663
00:52:53,280 --> 00:52:54,380
Mister!

664
00:52:54,840 --> 00:52:57,980
- The hospital. We have to get there now.
- Right.

665
00:53:26,710 --> 00:53:28,940
(Pit-a-Pat Butcher Restaurant)

666
00:54:00,980 --> 00:54:02,080
Don't worry.

667
00:54:03,650 --> 00:54:05,050
It's all over now.

668
00:54:06,550 --> 00:54:07,550
Okay.

669
00:54:28,900 --> 00:54:31,840
The phone is turned off. Please
leave a message after the tone...

670
00:54:33,640 --> 00:54:34,840
Why is it off?

671
00:54:37,180 --> 00:54:38,580
I hope nothing's happened to him.

672
00:54:44,850 --> 00:54:47,860
(Seoin Hospital)

673
00:54:50,990 --> 00:54:52,960
(Emergency Medical Center)

674
00:54:58,530 --> 00:55:00,170
Emergency patient! We need help out here.

675
00:55:17,290 --> 00:55:19,790
- Sir! Are you okay?
- Sir, sir! Stay with me!

676
00:55:21,090 --> 00:55:22,366
Emergency! Clear a path!

677
00:55:22,390 --> 00:55:25,106
Sir! Can you hear me?
Try to open your eyes. Sir!

678
00:55:25,130 --> 00:55:27,760
- Coming through!
- Sir, try to stay with us!

679
00:55:31,230 --> 00:55:32,230
What do we have?

680
00:55:32,630 --> 00:55:34,240
Penetrating wound to the right flank.

681
00:55:34,600 --> 00:55:37,510
- Vitals unstable from massive blood loss.
- Where's his family?

682
00:55:37,840 --> 00:55:39,160
We're trying to contact them now.

683
00:55:44,750 --> 00:55:45,810
Hello?

684
00:55:45,910 --> 00:55:48,950
I'm calling from Seoin Hospital.
Do you know Mr. Shin Yi Rang?

685
00:55:49,820 --> 00:55:50,920
Yes, I do.

686
00:55:51,420 --> 00:55:53,980
Mr. Shin Yi Rang was brought
in, and he's in critical condition.

687
00:55:54,220 --> 00:55:55,990
We found this number on his necklace and...

688
00:55:57,290 --> 00:55:59,690
Hello? Hello?

689
00:56:00,700 --> 00:56:01,700
I'm on my way.

690
00:56:02,730 --> 00:56:03,730
I'll be right there.

691
00:56:07,800 --> 00:56:10,570
(Okcheon Building)

692
00:56:10,870 --> 00:56:12,070
Hey, Han.

693
00:56:14,510 --> 00:56:16,310
Listen, there's something
I need to tell you.

694
00:56:18,280 --> 00:56:19,280
What's wrong?

695
00:56:22,650 --> 00:56:24,420
What's wrong? What happened? Tell me.

696
00:56:26,090 --> 00:56:27,220
Yi Rang is...

697
00:56:27,960 --> 00:56:28,960
What about Shin Yi Rang?

698
00:56:30,190 --> 00:56:31,390
He's at the hospital.

699
00:56:32,330 --> 00:56:33,360
I have to go.

700
00:56:34,030 --> 00:56:35,860
You're going to drive like this?

701
00:56:36,230 --> 00:56:37,970
I'm telling you, I have to get to Yi Rang.

702
00:56:57,290 --> 00:57:00,320
- I'm going to wipe this clean. Okay.
- Wipe right here, please.

703
00:57:01,390 --> 00:57:02,466
- Bong Soo.
- Yes?

704
00:57:02,490 --> 00:57:05,260
- Call Yi Rang and ask when he's home.
- Sure. Right away.

705
00:57:07,300 --> 00:57:10,670
(Emergency Medical Center)

706
00:57:13,500 --> 00:57:16,540
- Excuse me, where is Shin Yi Rang?
- Are you his next of kin?

707
00:57:17,970 --> 00:57:22,010
I'm so sorry, but he was already
unconscious when he was brought in...

708
00:57:35,320 --> 00:57:36,320
No.

709
00:57:46,000 --> 00:57:47,570
I should have been there.

710
00:57:51,070 --> 00:57:53,680
I should have been there with him.

711
00:58:45,230 --> 00:58:46,230
What's this?

712
00:58:47,530 --> 00:58:50,670
Don't tell me... Am I dead?

713
00:58:56,340 --> 00:58:57,410
I...

714
00:58:59,470 --> 00:59:01,310
Am I really dead?

715
00:59:24,770 --> 00:59:29,600
(Phantom Lawyer)

716
00:59:29,670 --> 00:59:31,746
- Yi Rang. Honey, Mom's here!
- Doctor!

717
00:59:31,770 --> 00:59:32,946
I'm begging you, please.

718
00:59:32,970 --> 00:59:35,210
We've already attempted
CPR several times, but...

719
00:59:35,310 --> 00:59:38,050
- Mister, please don't go.
- Who are you?

720
00:59:38,110 --> 00:59:39,856
- No.
- Who am I?

721
00:59:39,880 --> 00:59:41,296
Our Si Ho will be fine.

722
00:59:41,320 --> 00:59:44,126
They say Jo Chi Yeong is
pleading the fifth about Si Ho.

723
00:59:44,150 --> 00:59:46,626
- I don't know who Si Ho is.
- Then he must be completely insane.

724
00:59:46,650 --> 00:59:49,536
- Because there isn't enough evidence yet.
- What do you know?

725
00:59:49,560 --> 00:59:52,730
You promised you'd find my mom.
